-! # how to errors: 062-zsx-mismatched-tag.zo
-!
-! @cmd: `zo build 062-zsx-mismatched-tag.zo`
-!
-! #template
-!
-! A ZSX tag is like a specialized room. If you enter through a `<div>`, 
-! you cannot exit through a `</span>`. They are two different 
-! dimensions of data.
-!
-! In the "Great Divide" of the old web, this might go unnoticed or 
-! lead to a broken layout. In Zo, we catch the "Wrong Exit" during 
-! the build so your workstation stays solid.

fun main() {
  -- Mistake: Opening a <div> but trying to close with a </span>.
  imu view: </> ::= <div>"Mismatched Exit"</span>;
}

-! ## The Diagnostic:
-! Zo's parser remembers the "Open" tag and compares it to the "Close" 
-! tag. If they don't match, it identifies both so you can see 
-! the discrepancy.
-!
-! - **For the Human:** You're trying to close a box with the wrong lid.
-! - **For the Agent:** Error [E0062]. Open: `<div>` (Col 19). 
-!   Close: `</span>` (Col 37). Action: Match close to open.

-! ## Try this:
-! 
-! 1. **The Fix:** Change `</span>` to `</div>`. 
-! 2. **The Reverse:** Change the opening `<div>` to `<span>`. 
-!    Notice how the error stays consistent—they must always be a pair.
-! 3. **The Philosophy:** Symmetry is speed. Total Control.

-- EXPECTED OUTPUT:
-- [E0062] Error: Mismatched ZSX tags
--    ┌─ 062-zsx-mismatched-tag.zo:16:19
--    │
-- 16 │   imu view: </> = <div>"Mismatched Exit"</span>;
--    │                   ──┬──                 ──┬───
--    │                     │                     ╰── mismatched closing tag
--    │                     ╰── opened as `<div>` here
--    │
--    = Note: The closing tag must exactly match the name of the opening tag.
--    = Help: Change the `</span>` to `</div>` at line 16, column 37.
-- ────╯
